The issue is that whenever nodes have their size changed, either by calling the function or a container that have changed children, the node always expands to the right and bottom.

Instead it should be depended on the anchor points, for example, in the horizontal dimension:
- if anchor are both "begin" then it should expand to right;
- if anchor are both "end" then it should expand to the left instead, respecting the right or end margin;
- if anchor are both "center" or mixed, they expand equally the same to both sizes, respecting central position on the parent.

It fails to create a object :(

